1.title: Instructions
1.content:
Your task

Hello! This experiment has three parts.

It involves searching letters and estimating the difficulty of different search tasks.

In the last two parts of the experiment you will earn points. If your final point count is at the top 30% of our participants, you will receive a bonus of $0.75

19.title: estimation_feedback
19.content:
For this first estimation, you estimated that it will take you _estimate_ seconds to find 1 among 10 randomly positioned 's.
If you will find the in _estimate_ seconds or less in part 3 of the experiment, you will get _num_points_ points. Otherwise, you will get nothing. Your final number of points will determine whether you get a bonus or not.

21.title: Instructions2a
21.content:
Part 2

Good, you finished the first part!

Now, you will estimate how long it will take you to find various letters when mixed with different distractor letters.

22.title: Instructions3
22.content:
Part 3

You finished the second part!

In the third and last part of the experiment, you will perform three repetition of each search for which you gave a time estimate. Try to be as fast and accurate as possible, as your bonus depends on this! Just like in the first part, there's no time pressure on pressing the number key, but only on pressing the spacebar.

23.title: Instructions1a
23.content:
Part 1

In the first part, you will find target letters among distractor letters.

Some of the letters are from the Latin Alphabet, and others are made up letters from the Futurama TV series.

First, the target letter will appear on the screen. Remember it, as this is the letter you should find. Then, a gray cross will appear, and then the target and distractor letters will appear in random positions on an imaginary circle. When you spot the target letter, press spacebar as quickly as possible.

Upon pressing the spacebar, the target and distractors will disappear and be replaced by up to 5 numbers, one of which will appear where the target was displayed. To move to the next trial, type in the number that replaced the target.

25.content:
Thank you for your time!

We will appreciate any thoughts or comments you have about the experiment. You can use the box below to share them with us. Thank you!

35.title: Instructions2b
35.content:
Part 2

In each trial, you will estimate how long it will take you to find a letter when mixed with other letters presented in a square. The specific positions of the target and distractor letters on the imaginary circle are likely to change in the search phase, so focus on the identity of the letters.

Be as accurate as possible. In the third part, you will perform these searching tasks, and receive points only if you find the target letter as fast or faster than your estimate. The number of points offered for each estimate will appear inside the circle.

The small black arrows mark your search times from the first part of the experiment.

36.title: Instructions1b
36.content:
Part 1

Be quick to press the spacebar. There's no time pressure on pressing the right number key. At the end of each trial, you will get feedback about your accuracy and speed. Then, the next trial will begin.

Let's start!
